item.title: About
item.dc:creator: stekennedy_1993
item.excerpt:encoded: My love for Web and Graphic Design began when I first came into contact with it. When I was young, I always felt creative but I was never able to express it through illustration. I felt like I just wasn't good enough. It wasn't until I was older that I came across a Multimedia course and my passion for it grew from there. It gave me a platform in which I could create. I hope I can bring my creations to you. Enjoy my work!

item.title: Dublin Pride
item.dc:creator: stekennedy_1993
item.content:encoded:
Head Photographer for Dublin Pride 2016.

The role involved recruiting a team of photographers for the Dublin Pride Event of 2016 and working closely with Dublin Pride's Communications Manager (Eoin Hendrick) to ensure that each organisation in the Pride march is represented. Other roles included:
  • Mapping and assigning photographers to different areas of the parade.
  • Photographing the event itself alongside three other photographers.
  • Organising each photographers photos.
  • Processing, correcting, and editing of all photos taken between the team - (10,000 photos).
  • Photographing other events that spanned across the week long event.

item.title: FitSwap - Branding Project
item.dc:creator: stekennedy_1993
item.content:encoded:
College Graphic Design assignment.

Intro
The branding project is a college based assignment from the Brand Identity module in Creative Digital Media. At the start of this project, we are automatically assignment to a start-up company which we work together with for the semester in order to create said startup's brand. The startup I was paired with was a company that didn't originally have a name - the function of the company was to create a platform in which gym members could rent and sell their memberships through an app.   Through various brainstorming methods like the example shown above, I was able to devise a name for the brand which is 'FitSwap'. The inspiration for the name 'FitSwap' derived from the interaction method users would pursue in order to receive or rent their memberships e.g they swap money for their gym membership and vice versa. After much consideration, I conducted research and found that no twitter account or .com/.net domain was specifically registered to that plus no Facebook page was registered as Fitswap either.   [gallery size="large" ids="1338,1337,1336"] We were then tasked with designing three concept logos, a Creative Brief and a Visual Research PDF. The creative brief entailed creating a well-designed research document in which we investigated possible competitors for our startup company, introduction to the brand, the general ethos and the values of the company itself etc.  

After presenting the three logos to the client plus the Creative Brief, the client chose a logo and gave feedback on how they would like it modified. We would then meet back a week later to present the modified version of the logo. Above is the chosen logo and the modification based off client feedback.

After another client feedback session, we modified and proposed our master logo (shown above) and designed a Brand Guideline Document to go with the logo along with a final Visual PDF to document how we finalised the logo.

item.title: Response - Short Documentary
item.dc:creator: stekennedy_1993
item.content:encoded:
My roles in the project: Director of Photography. Cameraman. Blogger. Interviewer.

Response is a 10-minute short documentary highlighting the work of two search and rescue organisations in Ireland; Drogheda River Rescue & Recovery and Waterford Marine Search & Rescue. The documentary focuses on the people in these organisations, as well as their work in suicide prevention within their local communities. I took the role of director and lead editor in the project, as well as contributing to graphic elements of the project additional filming of footage.

WINNER OF ‘BEST 2ND YEAR GROUP PROJECT 2015’

Institute of Technology Blanchardstown
The ‘Second Year Group Project’ is a year-long project in the Creative Digital Media course, in which, over the course of the academic year, groups of 4 are tasked with completing a  large project - or in our case a ten-minute short documentary. These projects can be video-based, website development and design, animation, or rebranding and graphic design. Our short documentary, ‘Response’, was awarded as joint-winner along with a short animation.

item.title: Parallax Design
item.dc:creator: stekennedy_1993
item.content:encoded:
2nd Year College Web Design assignment.

To better demonstrate the project, a set of gifs have been used to illustrate the project's functionality. The scrolling parallax assignment involved making a personal parallax website without using frameworks or templates. For the task, we also had to make the project more personal - it had to be something in relation to one of our hobbies or passions and it had to include some slight animations. For the project, I chose to do one of my hobbies: photography. The mockup assignment aimed to highlight my inspirations, passions, and some of my work. All photos featured on the website are my own.
